pr_review_body:
@xiaohu2015 Thanks for the PR.

Unfortunately we want to avoid coupling CutMix and Mixup with the loss. This was discussed back when the transforms were introduced, see https://github.com/pytorch/vision/pull/4379#discussion_r705281765. Note that label smoothing is already supported in our training scripts because PyTorch Core's CrossEntropyLoss can operate with smooth labels and accepts a `label_smoothing` parameter.

Also please note, even thought it's not strictly mandatory to raise an issue prior to sending a PR, it does help to discuss the details of more complicated features. This avoids throwaway work, gives context to the team during code review and maximizes the chance of merging.

@samuelcolvin, please beware that this PR introduces breaking changes

This was previously a valid usecase, but with these changes it will raise an error:
```py
def test_custom_getter_dict():
    class TestCls:
        x = 1
        y = 2

    def custom_getter_dict(obj):
        assert isinstance(obj, TestCls)
        return {'x': 42, 'y': 24}
```

Can we add some tests for this as well? An integration test like [`tests/integration/dynamic/python`](https://github.com/pulumi/pulumi/tree/master/tests/integration/dynamic/python) should work. To add a test, you can just copy that folder to a new folder (e.g. `tests/integration/dynamic/python-type-name`) and add a new test method to `tests/integration/integration_python_test.go`, e.g. by copying and modifying the method for [`tests/integration/dynamic/python`](https://github.com/pulumi/pulumi/blob/master/tests/integration/integration_python_test.go#L389-L408).

Please let me know if you need any more info on how to add a test!

@lukehoban I think that we can file a follow-up issue for Node.

Lots of changes. So, this is a major refactoring job.
Probably it would be a good idea to change the title;
`Add {set,get}_bucket_versioning() APIs`

This PR is interesting because it does add some features to env vars which is interesting, but it does seem to add a bit of complexity (`+436 −178`) to ultimately make it so that we can override a default plugins directory.

It's my preference if there a way to add a default plugins directory env var without making too many changes here.

@Frassle I know you tend to have opinions on things like these. WDYT?

What about just sorting and popping? E.g.,

```
i = 0

while (i < next_index) {
    // Append  the first entry to the end until the next index
    buffer_.append(buffer_.pop(0))
    i += 1
}
next_index = 0

reported = 0
to_send = []
while (reported < batch_size) {
    to_send.append(buffer_.pop(0))
}
```

@100sun
In order to pass the GitHub action, you may need to apply news fragment file inside [`/changes`](https://github.com/lablup/backend.ai/tree/main/changes)
Please refer to the README there and apply it.
